<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40145c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40145c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40145c"> 145(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> talismanic / garments </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Commonly throughout the pre-modern Turko-Persian world, miniature calligraphic script was regularly placed against the body through its inscripotion on talismanic shirts or garments, typically made of cotton, linen, or silk and contextualized with prayers, Qur&apos;anic verses, names of God, alphanumeric magical squares, onomantic numeric formulas, and suchlike, woven into, or painted or written upon, the entire surface with multihued paints and inks by courtly artisans and calligraphers. These garments were commonly worn into war, but also during occasions of trial or stress (such as childbirth). </mm> </dd></dl>
